https://www.evosounds.com 

Today, were diving into one of the most powerful new features in Serum 2 the Multisample & Sampler section.

This episode is all about understanding how multisampling works, why it matters for modern sound design, and how you can use it to blend organic textures with rich synth tones to create more expressive, musical patches.

 What youll learn in Episode 2:
How the multisample engine works inside Serum 2
Why multisampling is clutch for bringing realism, depth, and movement into your synth sounds
How I use multisampling in my own sound design workflow when creating packs  including sampling my analog synths and turning them into playable instruments
What .sfc files are, why they matter, and how to create your own
How to get the most out of the updated Sampler section
Layering, blending, and mixing techniques to combine organic + electronic elements seamlessly
A full sound design session at the end where we make a couple of fire patches using only the multisample and sampler tools

Whether youre designing your own instruments from scratch or looking to elevate the realism and emotion of your sounds, the multisample update in Serum 2 is a game-changer  and today youll learn exactly how to use it.
